        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>E. Eppstein<lb/>
                439 N. Sixth St.								Quincy Ill. Octob. 15. 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. Fifth St.<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. dear Sir and Friend&#59;<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr. I. Seider &#40;a Russian&#41; residing here these<lb/> eight years&#44; supporting himself and family com&#45;<lb/>fortably&#44; called on me this noon&#44; stating that a<lb/> brother of his wife Mr. Eieel &#40;Ezeckiel&#41; Gietelman<lb/> 23 yrs. of age&#44; married&#45;&#45;no children&#45;&#45;&#44; a carpenter<lb/> by trade&#44; left his home&#44; Russia&#44; and arrived at the<lb/> Port of Philadelphia some six weeks ago.  Having been<lb/> sick for some time after his arrival&#44; the young man<lb/> could not obtain sufficient work to support himself<lb/> and remit same to his wife and depending mother.<lb/>  His brother&#45;in&#45;law now claims that if his relative<lb/> could come us here&#44; he would find paying and<lb/> constant employment in one of the many factories<lb/> established here&#59; thus enabling him to support<lb/> his family.  The young man board at 423 Arch<lb/> Str.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Asking my <sic>advise</sic>&#44; I thought this to be a case<lb/> falling under the workings of the &#34;Baron de Hirsch&#34;<lb/> Trust.  The man stands in need of the necessary funds<lb/> to travel West and implements of his trade.  For this<lb/> reason I gave Mr. Seidler this letter for his brother&#44;<lb/> which he shall hand to you in person&#44; so you will be<lb/> able to judge for yourself&#44; whether the man is worthy<lb/> the assistance asked.  It seems to me that with the<lb/> B. &#38; O. the ticket may be purchased at a cheap rate&#44;<lb/> Forty Dolls. will&#44; I think&#44; cover the whole case.<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr. Seidler&#44; I know to be a man of integrity<lb/> upon whose statement I can rely.<lb/>
                With my best Regards<lb/> Yours ty<lb/> E Eppstein.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
